The program is useful in cases when you need to break
data into categoriesand collect relevant statistics.

At startup, all the data that the user passes through
the standard input stream or through a text file is read.

The resulting text is divided into words to determine
the frequency of occurrence of each word. After that,
it is placed in the standard output stream, or in a
text file specified at startup.

The output data format is a table of the form:

┌───────────┬────────────────┬────────────────────┐
│   index   │    frequency   │        word        │
├───────────┼────────────────┼────────────────────┘
| ...       | ...            | ...
└───────────┴────────────────┴────────────────────┘
